  "prompt": "What does \"dying from exposure\" mean?",
  "response": "\"Dying from exposure\" refers to death resulting from prolonged exposure to harsh environmental conditions. This can include extreme temperatures\u2014either very cold or very hot\u2014severe weather, or other elements that the human body cannot withstand for extended periods. In cases of cold exposure, this might involve hypothermia or frostbite, where the body's core temperature drops dangerously low. In cases of heat exposure, it could involve heatstroke or dehydration, where the body becomes overheated and loses too much fluid. Other factors, like lack of proper shelter, clothing, or access to medical care, can exacerbate the risks associated with exposure to the environment.",
